result.name: Bluebird Coffee

reviews.text:
Bluebird offers a tea set (on week days?) with a choice of coffee and a piece of cake.  I have picked a latte with oat milk and a strawberry cheesecake; a pretty good combination between nutty coffee and creamy cheesecake.  Particularly impressed by the fresh strawberries and the sauce.
A pretty nice place for a coffee break.

After a meeting in Sheung Wan, I managed to pop in Bluebird Coffee 15 minutes before it closes, and that’s why I ordered a Flat White to go instead of dining in, though I would really love to dine in so that I can enjoy the coffee shop vibes and save the environment (I know…I forgot to bring my reusable coffee cup…).

There are three sizes for Flat White, “Short”, “Tall” and “Large”. This Tall Flat White is quite pricey (HKD$48) compared to other coffee shops. It was a bit disappointing that there was no latte art for my to-go coffee, whilst other hearty coffee shops do that even for take away. The coffee was just okay, not fruity nor chocolaty, just aromatic.

When I got to Bluebird, there were no seats so I stood outside to wait for my friend and then someone who looks like the owner came out to ask if wanted to sit outside since there is more space. Being deathly attractive to mosquitoes and with a thunderstorm warning on the horizon, I kindly declined and said I would just wait for my friend. She said no worries and that a table should free up in the next several minutes. And she was right! One of the tables left and she immediately bussed it for me. I ordered their flat white, my go-to, and I enjoyed the richness of the coffee. Overall, my experience here was good and would recommend it if you're in the area.

Nice atmosphere and warm service. The quality of coffee is high with many choices. There's even peanut butter latte! I pretty enjoyed the homemade cheesecake as well, smooth and balanced. Such a cozy place to take a rest and have a sip of coffee.

Simply in love with this hidden gem! 
So impressed by the fragrance of their specialty coffee- peanut butter latte! Their homemade cheesecake tastes very rich and goes perfectly well with their coffee! 
I will definitely be back;)

reviews.text: 搶眼的鮮藍店面，內搭粉藍設計，食物和咖啡味道不錯，兩者的種類有大型連鎖咖啡店的影子，缺點是店內座位太少(大約10個)，一眼已盡覽整間店。

Bluebird offers a tea set (on week days?) with a choice of coffee and a piece of cake.  I have picked a latte with oat milk and a strawberry cheesecake; a pretty good combination between nutty coffee and creamy cheesecake.  Particularly impressed by the fresh strawberries and the sauce.
A pretty nice place for a coffee break.

藍色俾人舒服自在既感覺，+多杯咖啡更能脫離繁忙城市，走向慢活... Bluebird coffee 係西環近A出口一間新間既coffee 鮮明藍色既外牆，遙遠已可見。小店不太大，但可容納10多人，簡單舒服既環境，最岩談心... 主打咖啡係手沖咖啡，咖啡來自唔同國家，例如哥倫比亞 巴西等既高質咖啡豆，可買杯袋液可買走咖啡豆自沖。 
我叫左杯Cobalt , 係齋啡來，純而易入口，咖啡味濃而不太苦澀，有別於其他齋啡，適合適合人。

朋友叫左sunrise 都係齋啡，但口感清d，遍酸，同時易入口呀。

朱古力酥最後一件俾我order左 皮脆內軟朱古力餡微甜 配齋啡我覺得好夾。

齋啡聽講可以抗自由基，消水腫，做gym 前飲杯齋啡可增加燃燒脂肪.....但對我而言有作舒緩m痛🙈😂

After a meeting in Sheung Wan, I managed to pop in Bluebird Coffee 15 minutes before it closes, and that’s why I ordered a Flat White to go instead of dining in, though I would really love to dine in so that I can enjoy the coffee shop vibes and save the environment (I know…I forgot to bring my reusable coffee cup…).

There are three sizes for Flat White, “Short”, “Tall” and “Large”. This Tall Flat White is quite pricey (HKD$48) compared to other coffee shops. It was a bit disappointing that there was no latte art for my to-go coffee, whilst other hearty coffee shops do that even for take away. The coffee was just okay, not fruity nor chocolaty, just aromatic.

nutella latte
如果平時吾系好鐘意飲太苦嘅咖啡 尼杯就岩哂你 雖然佢系nutella但你可以放心佢一啲都吾會太甜 我覺得佢吾會苦但又帶到咖啡個陣味 同埋nutella latte我都系第一次見 我覺得都好特

Hand drip coffee
我揀左呢個Colombia El Progreso咖啡豆試下 據說呢款豆評分有87分 飲落豆香好濃 真系好似張卡咁講有種淡淡既菊花味 我好驚飲啲咖啡好苦好澀 而呢款就完全一啲都唔苦 我好中意

cheese spinach pie
如果你去嘅話一定要試尼個pie勁好食 佢酥皮又夠脆 本身spinach 嘅批已經好少見 佢啲芝士份量岩岩好吾會好膩吾會淨系食到芝士味 佢仲批當然系焗左先比你放心佢系吾會有starbucks翻熱 熱得濟嘅問題👍🏼 .
.
